{{Infobox officeholder | name = George Gigicos | image = | caption = | office = White House Scheduling and Advance Director | president = [[Donald Trump]] | term_start = January 20, 2017 | term_end = July 31, 2017 | predecessor = Chase Cushman | successor = [[Jordan Karem]] | party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = [[Birmingham–Southern College]] | occupation = }} '''George Gigicos''' is an American campaign consultant who specializes in advance representation for Republican politicians. He served as White House Scheduling and Advance Director<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/donald-trump-administration/2016/11/trump-adds-vice-chairs-to-transition-team-including-several-women-231975|title=Trump adds vice chairs to transition team, including several women|work=POLITICO|access-date=2017-03-25}}</ref> from the beginning of [[Donald Trump]]'s presidency until July 31, 2017.<ref name="GigicosLeaves">{{cite web |last=Gray |first=Noah |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/08/02/politics/george-gigicos-white-house/index.html |title=Longtime Trump advance man leaves administration |work=[[CNN]] |date=August 2, 2017 |accessdate=August 5, 2017}}</ref><ref name="Bloomberg">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/amp/news/articles/2017-08-28/trump-is-said-to-punish-longtime-aide-after-angry-phoenix-speech |title=Trump Punishes Longtime Aide After Angry Phoenix Speech, Sources Say |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829125822/https://www.bloomberg.com/amp/news/articles/2017-08-28/trump-is-said-to-punish-longtime-aide-after-angry-phoenix-speech |archive-date=August 29, 2017 |date=August 28, 2017 |publisher=[[Bloomberg News]] |first=Jennifer |last=Jacobs |first2=Kevin |last2=Cirilli |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Biography== Gigicos is of [[Greece|Greek]] descent and has ancestry from [[Kalamata]]. He studied at [[Birmingham–Southern College]] in Alabama, graduating in 1990. Gigicos worked in advance planning for the [[United States Department of the Treasury]] under President [[George H. W. Bush]] and later worked as an event planner at the [[Orange County Convention Center]] in Florida. He founded a communications firm known as the Telion Corporation in 1999, and also worked for the Republican campaigns of [[George W. Bush]], [[John McCain]], and [[Mitt Romney]].<ref name=greek>{{cite web|url=http://usa.greekreporter.com/2017/01/05/donald-trump-appoints-greek-american-george-gigicos-deputy-assistant-to-the-president/|title=Donald Trump Appoints Greek-American George Gigicos Deputy Assistant to the President|author=Chrysopoulos, Philip|newspaper=[[Greek Reporter]]|date=January 5, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017}}</ref>
===Trump Administration=== In December 2016, ''[[Politico]]'' reported that Gigicos was one of Trump's campaign staffers being considered for a staff role in the Trump administration. The site reported that Gigicos was likely to be appointed as the director of White House advance. Trump appointed him as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of Advance on January 5, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2016/12/donald-trump-white-house-team-232543|title=Trump close to building out senior White House team|work=POLITICO|access-date=2017-03-25}}</ref> He served in the Trump Administration until July 31, 2017.<ref name="GigicosLeaves"/>
